Graeme Smith and Mark Boucher. JOHANNESBURG - Cricket South Africa have admitted they did consider suspending both Director of Cricket Graeme Smith and Proteas coach Mark Boucher following allegations made against the pair at the SJN hearings. Smith and Boucher had allegations of discrimination levelled against them, while their employment has also been questioned but cricket bosses decided not to suspend the pair, although Boucher faces a disciplinary hearing. READ: Date set for Boucher's disciplinary hearing Board Chairperson Lawson Naidoo explains why in the video below.  Cricket South Africa have admitted they did consider suspending both Director of Cricket, Graeme Smith and Proteas coach Mark Boucher following allegations made against the pair at the SJN hearings. Smith and Boucher had allegations of discrimination levelled against them. #eNCA pic.twitter.com/wJznJlzMcZ